  "section_name": "Financial Analysis",
  "text": "Adobe maintains substantial R&D investment intensity at 17.73% of revenue in Q4 (K007), with R&D expenses of $1,098,000,000 (C016) against revenue of $6,194,000,000 (C010). This elevated investment level reflects the company's commitment to advancing its AI-powered capabilities across the Creative Cloud, Document Cloud, and Experience Cloud portfolios. R&D spending has grown sequentially from $1,082,000,000 in Q2 (C032) to $1,088,000,000 in Q3 (C024) and $1,098,000,000 in Q4 (C016), demonstrating sustained commitment to innovation. While this intensity pressures near-term operating margins, it positions Adobe competitively in the rapidly evolving generative AI landscape and supports long-term product differentiation.",
